<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Dalepak jumps 42% at midway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
'DESPITE the economic conditions being the worst in Dalepak Foods' 16-year
history', the food manufacturer continued its steady progress with a 42 per
cent jump in pre-tax profits in the six months to October 31 1991.
In the corresponding period they rose by 71 per cent and in the year to
April 30 1991 by 57 per cent.
This time taxable profits of Pounds 1.71m (Pounds 1.2m) were struck on
turnover fractionally ahead at Pounds 21.2m (Pounds 21.1m). Turnover in
continuing activities was up 15 per cent, with Dalepak and Fawcetts, the
frozen food businesses, rising 14 and 16 per cent respectively.
The company said that its traditional meat grillsteak market grew 8 per cent
in the half after several years of decline. The markets for its
vegetable-based products grew rapidly, stimulated by new product launches
and heavy marketing expenditure.
The interest bill fell to Pounds 15,000 (Pounds 148,000) and earnings
emerged at 10.13p (6.99p) per share. The interim dividend is lifted to 1.5p
(1.2p), an increase of 25 per cent.
</TEXT>
