</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR David Hunt, Welsh secretary, told the Commons yesterday that the average
poll tax should be 'around Pounds 100' in Wales in the coming financial
year.
He also announced that the increase in the business rate poundage would be
limited to 4.1 per cent.
Mr Barry Jones, the shadow Welsh secretary, dismissed the forecast level of
