<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 92 / International Company News: First Chicago registers Dollars
15m loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BARBARA DURR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FIRST Chicago, the holding company for First National Bank of Chicago,
posted a fourth-quarter loss of Dollars 15.1m, or 40 cents per share,
compared with earnings of Dollars 57.1m or 75 cents per share a year ago.
Annual earnings for 1991 were Dollars 116.3m, or Dollars 1.15 per share,
down by more than half from Dollars 249.3m, or Dollars 3.32, in 1990.
The fourth-quarter results were hit by a Dollars 150m provision for credit
losses, primarily for two loans in retailing and communications. Another
Dollars 30m was set aside as loss provisions for other real estate assets.
Non-performing assets fell by Dollars 300m at the end of 1991 from their
peak of Dollars 1.6bn. The bank reduced its quarterly dividend to 30 cents
from 50 cents.
</TEXT>
