<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 92 / UK Company News: US operations take toll on Quiligotti
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON-FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
QUILIGOTTI, the USM-quoted manufacturer and installer of terrazzo floors
based in Stockport, has incurred an attributable loss of Pounds 1.11m after
paying compensation of Pounds 371,000 net to its previous family directors
in the wake of an Pounds 8m management buy-in last September, writes Ian
Hamilton-Fazey.
In November the company said there would be a trading loss of Pounds 444,000
in the six months to September 30, because operations in the US lost Pounds
860,000 and more than wiped out profits of Pounds 672,000 in Britain and
Ireland, and because of Pounds 256,000 bad debts provision.
However, the full interim figures announced yesterday revealed a pre-tax
loss of Pounds 646,000 (profit Pounds 1.08m) after an exceptional Pounds
202,000 for reorganisation of the UK business. To this is added compensation
for the Quiligotti family - founding father and two sons - which is charged
in the accounts as an extraordinary Pounds 371,000 net of tax; gross
payments being nearly Pounds 571,000. The buy-in team initially hoped to
work with the family.
Losses per share were 2.53p (earnings 2.41p) and the interim dividend is
passed (0.76p).
</TEXT>
